WEBVTT

00:02.737 --> 00:05.004
Now you're having
second thoughts.
                       Says who?

00:05.006 --> 00:06.438
Your tone of voice,
your body language.

00:06.440 --> 00:08.290
                  That's not so.

00:08.291 --> 00:10.141
     Yeah, it is. It's like
   you're folding your tent.

00:10.144 --> 00:11.610
        I just got stuck
    on his age for a minute.

00:11.612 --> 00:13.278
  You may have a point there.

00:13.280 --> 00:15.180
        Of course I got
  a point there-- he's green.

00:15.182 --> 00:16.615
    He's the preeminent guy
         in his thing.

00:16.617 --> 00:19.752
         No 25-year-old
   is preeminent in anything.

00:19.754 --> 00:21.420
     So you don't like him
       because of his age

00:21.422 --> 00:22.621
Or because of who he works for?

00:22.623 --> 00:25.424
      You asked me to look
    into their work, I did.

00:25.426 --> 00:28.794
One man's opinion-- it's green,
     because they're green.

00:28.796 --> 00:30.596
            And you're using
              green wrong.
   What?

00:30.598 --> 00:32.164
              Green doesn't mean
          inexperienced anymore.

00:32.165 --> 00:33.399
                        It means
                   eco-friendly.

00:33.401 --> 00:34.951
I know that.

00:34.952 --> 00:36.502
Are we publishing
this conversation?
                      No, but...

00:36.504 --> 00:37.770
Well, as long as
you know

00:37.772 --> 00:40.439
What I mean by green,
then green'll do.

00:40.441 --> 00:42.408
         Were you green
       when you were 25?

00:42.410 --> 00:43.776
No.
        But everyone else is.

00:43.778 --> 00:45.611
I didn't say that.
                 I take it back.

00:45.613 --> 00:47.312
         You don't have a point
             about his age.

00:47.314 --> 00:48.580
   Look, I already said yes.

00:48.582 --> 00:51.183
  Let's just see how it flies.

00:51.185 --> 00:52.184
             Why does everything
                      have to be

00:52.186 --> 00:53.185
      Like pulling teeth?

00:53.187 --> 00:54.186
  You're a good egg, garrett.

00:54.188 --> 00:56.255
    I just want to make sure

00:56.256 --> 00:58.323
    That egg doesn't end up
       all over our face.

00:58.325 --> 00:59.658
      Is that why you put
     office reagan on this?

00:59.660 --> 01:01.326
          As insurance
      against my judgment?

01:01.328 --> 01:03.395
      I put jamie on this
      because he can read

01:03.397 --> 01:06.465
  A potential situation better
      than anybody I know.

01:06.467 --> 01:07.366
 Because you don't trust me to.

01:07.368 --> 01:10.269
    Because it's sensitive.

01:10.271 --> 01:13.439
       Sir, city council
  just moved up their meeting.

01:13.441 --> 01:16.375
      It's now a conflict
  with your jim voutay lunch.

01:16.377 --> 01:18.277
              Oh.

01:19.180 --> 01:20.345
           He's here

01:20.347 --> 01:22.414
        For the council
   of university presidents.

01:22.416 --> 01:23.983
      I'll have to cancel.

01:23.984 --> 01:25.551
       After his school's
    undefeated football team

01:25.553 --> 01:27.152
 Wins a national championship?

01:27.154 --> 01:28.554
      That's a sacrilege.

01:28.556 --> 01:31.356
    Can you do me a favor--
      have lunch with him?

01:33.194 --> 01:35.427
       I'll see if I can
       clear my schedule.

01:35.429 --> 01:37.129
        Problem solved.

